groundTruth.text:
Abstract
                  Computed tomography (CT) is the preferred imaging method for diagnosing 2019 novel coronavirus (COVID19) pneumonia. We aimed to construct a system based on deep learning for detecting COVID-19 pneumonia on high resolution CT. For model development and validation, 46,096 anonymous images from 106 admitted patients, including 51 patients of laboratory confirmed COVID-19 pneumonia and 55 control patients of other diseases in Renmin Hospital of Wuhan University were retrospectively collected. Twenty-seven prospective consecutive patients in Renmin Hospital of Wuhan University were collected to evaluate the efficiency of radiologists against 2019-CoV pneumonia with that of the model. An external test was conducted in Qianjiang Central Hospital to estimate the system’s robustness. The model achieved a per-patient accuracy of 95.24% and a per-image accuracy of 98.85% in internal retrospective dataset. For 27 internal prospective patients, the system achieved a comparable performance to that of expert radiologist. In external dataset, it achieved an accuracy of 96%. With the assistance of the model, the reading time of radiologists was greatly decreased by 65%. The deep learning model showed a comparable performance with expert radiologist, and greatly improved the efficiency of radiologists in clinical practice.

problem.title: Automating Medical Image Diagnosis with Deep Learning for Improved Clinical Efficiency
problem.description: Developing reliable, scalable, and clinically interpretable deep learning systems to automate the diagnosis of complex medical conditions from imaging data (e.g., CT scans) while maintaining accuracy comparable to human experts. This challenge extends to other medical imaging modalities (e.g., MRI, X-ray) and diseases where early and accurate diagnosis is critical.

templateData.title: Deep Learning-Based Automated Medical Image Diagnosis: Technical Implementation Framework
templateData.description: A study reporting the design, evaluation, and deployment of deep learning systems in medical image diagnosis, emphasizing technical reproducibility, clinical interpretability, and performance benchmarking across imaging modalities (CT, MRI, X-ray).

templateProperty.label: Primary Dataset
templateProperty.description: medical imaging dataset(s) used for training/validation (e.g., NIH ChestX-ray14, BraTS, LIDC-IDRI).

templateProperty.label: Dataset Modality
templateProperty.description: Imaging modality(ies) targeted (e.g., CT, MRI, X-ray, Ultrasound).

templateProperty.label: Sample Size
templateProperty.description: Total number of annotated images/volumes in the dataset (training/validation/test splits).

templateProperty.label: Annotation Protocol
templateProperty.description: Methodology for ground truth generation (e.g., consensus of 3 radiologists, automated segmentation tools).

templateProperty.label: Model Architecture
templateProperty.description: Base deep learning architecture (e.g., ResNet-50, U-Net, Vision Transformer, nnU-Net).

templateProperty.label: Architecture Modifications
templateProperty.description: Custom layers or adaptations (e.g., attention mechanisms, skip connections, 3D convolutions).

templateProperty.label: Number of Parameters
templateProperty.description: Total trainable parameters in the model (report in millions).

templateProperty.label: Deep Learning Framework
templateProperty.description: Software framework used (e.g., PyTorch 2.0, TensorFlow 2.12, MONAI).

templateProperty.label: Preprocessing Steps
templateProperty.description: Pipeline for normalization, resizing, augmentation (e.g., CLIPD windowing for CT, bias field correction for MRI).

templateProperty.label: Training Hardware
templateProperty.description: GPU/TPU configuration (e.g., NVIDIA A100 80GB, Google TPU v4).

templateProperty.label: Batch Size
templateProperty.description: Batch size per GPU during training (report as integer).

templateProperty.label: Optimizer
templateProperty.description: Optimization algorithm (e.g., AdamW, SGD with momentum, Lion).

templateProperty.label: Learning Rate
templateProperty.description: Initial learning rate and schedule (e.g., 1e-4 with cosine decay).

templateProperty.label: Loss Function
templateProperty.description: Primary loss function (e.g., Dice + CE, focal loss, contrastive loss).

templateProperty.label: Training Epochs
templateProperty.description: Total epochs trained (report as integer).

templateProperty.label: Regularization Techniques
templateProperty.description: Methods to prevent overfitting (e.g., dropout 0.3, weight decay 1e-5, mixup).

templateProperty.label: Primary Metric
templateProperty.description: Main evaluation metric (e.g., AUC-ROC, Dice coefficient, sensitivity at 95% specificity).

templateProperty.label: Metric Value
templateProperty.description: Quantitative result for the primary metric (report as decimal between 0–1 or percentage).

templateProperty.label: Inference Time
templateProperty.description: Average time per image/volume in milliseconds (report as integer).

templateProperty.label: Interpretability Method
templateProperty.description: Technique for model explainability (e.g., Grad-CAM, SHAP, attention maps).

templateProperty.label: Clinical Validation
templateProperty.description: Description of prospective/retrospective clinical testing (e.g., reader study with 5 radiologists).

templateProperty.label: Deployment Framework
templateProperty.description: Tool for model serving (e.g., TensorRT, ONNX Runtime, NVIDIA Tritons).

templateProperty.label: Source Code Repository
templateProperty.description: Public link to implementation (GitHub, GitLab, etc.).

templateProperty.label: Paper DOI
templateProperty.description: Digital Object Identifier for the published work.
